cs.SI, cs.CL, cs.SOC, cs.CYBER, cs.IR 

This paper deals with analyzing digital traces of conversations in micro-blogging platforms and OSNs to understand and monitor collective behaviors. It proposes a method for tracking polarized users and topics over time on Twitter datasets during political election time-frames. This work involves natural language processing, social network analysis, and information retrieval techniques, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.SOC (Computational Social Science), cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
